<blockquote>
  <p>For commands, We canâ€™t simply say â€¦ if they evaluate to the same ending state
<strong>some commands donâ€™t terminate in any final state at all!</strong></p>
</blockquote>

<p>So to define, they either orâ€¦</p>
<ol>
  <li>both diverge éƒ½å‘æ•£</li>
  <li>both terminate in the same final state éƒ½åœ¨åŒä¸€ä¸ªçŠ¶æ€åœæœº</li>
</ol>

<p>A compact way is</p>
<blockquote>
  <p>â€œif the first one terminates in a particular state then so does the second, and vice versa.â€</p>
</blockquote>

