<h2 id="extended-exercise-nondeterministic-imp">Extended Exercise: Nondeterministic Imp</h2>

<blockquote>
  <p>HAVOC roughly corresponds to an <em>uninitialized variable</em> in a low-level language like C. 
After the HAVOC, the variable holds a fixed but arbitrary number.</p>
</blockquote>

